@rnveach @gaurabdg
No, I am saying about creating depth attribute for AbstractNode class,
So my suggestion is to initialize depth attribute during Xpath tree creation process instead of lazy calculations.
For example constructor of the ElementNode could be smth like
 public ElementNode(AbstractNode root, AbstractNode parent, DetailAST detailAst) {
        super(root.getTreeInfo());
        this.parent = parent;
        this.root = root;
        this.detailAst = detailAst;
        this.nodeDepth = parent.nodeDepth + 1; // <-- You can use parent's height
        text = TokenUtil.getTokenName(detailAst.getType());
        indexAmongSiblings = parent.getChildren().size();
        createTextAttribute();
        createChildren();
    }

Xpath tree construction is recursive DFS, so height of every child of the node is larger by one than the parent height
What do you think about it?

